#### Eye: short ophthalmology examples // examples subsection
// CLUSTER: high-yield eye pattern recognition and photo/exam prompts
{EXM-130, EX, EX_SHORT} - Open/Penetrating Eye Injury; H: Boy pain 3 days, stick in eye, vision bad, can't see back. Yellow in eye | Lad 2 days pain after eye injury, va poor, white line inside | Child with plant injury to eye, pain bad, vision decreased, yellow behind cornea. A: 🚩 Is the _pus_ at the bottom of the AC? If open injury suspected, use Arclight blue light and NaFl for a _tiny corneal leak_. Any peaked pupil towards the wound? [Emergency; no pressure on globe; Later: surgical washout, tetanus, Abx]
{EXM-140, EX, EX_SHORT} - Stevens-Johnson; H: Rash on face around eyes, sore lips | Facial red sores, sore mouth, look ill. A: 🚩 Any fever with skin peeling or blisters on mouth, eyes, genitals or skin? Check the whole body. [Emergency; Later: culprit drug review, eye protection/symblepharon care, fluids, pain relief]
{EXM-150, EX, EX_SHORT} - Giant Cell Arteritis; H: Old woman headache, jaw tired eating, vision less | Elderly Px with headache, jaw fatigue eating | Old, headache, jaw aches eating, vision gone. A: 🚩 Check general health: weight loss or fever? Look for _jaw, scalp or temple tenderness_ and a thick visible artery. [Emergency; polymyalgia rheumatica; Later: ESR/CRP, steroids]
{EXM-160, EX, EX_SHORT} - Amaurosis Fugax; H: Vision go few sec, then back OK | Brief vision loss, then back to normal. A: One eye or both? Any dizziness, weakness or speech trouble? Check blood pressure and do a full physical. [Urgent medical/stroke review; consider GCA with age, sickle cell]
{EXM-170, EX, EX_SHORT} - Preseptal / Orbital Cellulitis; H: Baby swollen red lid, vision seem OK | Young girl with puffy red eyelid, vision unaffected | Swollen red lid, VA normal. A: ⚠️ Is the whole eyelid swollen or just a lump? _Pain moving the eye_? Fever or insect bite? [Red if swollen shut, painful/restricted eye movement, proptosis, VA down or high fever; Later: hospital/Abx; malnutrition incr. risk]
{EXM-1440, EX, EX_SHORT} - Baby pus eye; H: 5wk baby has green from eye | 2 month old has pus out from eye, what I do? A: ⚠️ Is baby generally well or feverish? Are lids very swollen or is cornea cloudy? Check both eyes and ears. How many days has pus been present?
{EXM-190, EX, EX_SHORT} - Congenital Glaucoma; H: Baby eyes big, cloudy cornea, tearing lots | Infant obvious eyes, white corneas, spasm lids. A: 🚩 Has this been present since birth? Compare cloudy corneas and diameter; if able, check IOP, disc cupping or horizontal corneal breaks. [Epiphora, photophobia, Haab’s striae, blepharospasm]
{EXM-180, EX, EX_SHORT} - Retinoblastoma; H: Baby got big eye, mother worry | Infant enlarged eye. A: 🚩 Is the eye truly _big_, or just red/swollen? How long: days or weeks? With Arclight, check fundal reflex brightness/colour; any blood vessels, folds or 'lines' in pupil? Take your time. [White pupil, squint or enlarged eye = urgent; check FHx]
{EXM-200, EX, EX_SHORT} - Retinopathy of Prematurity; H: 4mth old, early birth and little weight, wobbly eyes | Sudden birth baby, 5 mth old now, still tiny, unsteady eyes. A: ⚠️ In _premature_ babies, birth weight matters. Do they follow faces or show 'silent smiles'? Examine the back of the eyes — any white patches? [Urgent; Later: BIO, laser/aVEGF; monitor for squint/myopia]
{EXM-210, EX, EX_SHORT} - Vitreous Haemorrhage; H: Sudden big dark area, not clear, moves around | Dark area vision, come quick, moving. A: ⚠️ One eye or both? Diabetic, injured or recent heavy physical work? Use Arclight to check for vitreous blood. [Ultrasound if available when fundus not visible; RAPD rule out RD/tear; bed rest w/ elevated head]
{EXM-220, EX, EX_SHORT} - Floaters; H: See small bit like flies, no pain | Little floaters, no pain | Tiny bits in sight like gnats, no pain. A: Sudden or gradual? One eye or both? Any _flashing lights_ or a new black area like a _curtain_? [PVD common in old/myopic/trauma; flash/curtain = RD]
{EXM-230, EX, EX_SHORT} - Macular Hole/FTMH; H: Old lady, quick dark patch in middle, few days ago | Woman, sudden central dark spot | Dark area in centre vision, man. A: Any injury, cataract surgery or bent straight lines? With Arclight, examine the macula/fovea for a hole or defect. [Amsler; sudden central vision loss w/ healthy disc suggests macular problem. RAPD?]
{EXM-240, EX, EX_SHORT} - Carotid-Cavernous Fistula; H: Sudden head noise, eye closed, red forehead patch | Abrupt sound in skull, eye shut, swelling on head. A: 🚩 Open the eye — any bright 'zig zag' red vessels? Does it feel _pulsating_? Check eye movements, lid droop and pupil size. ['Whooshing' bruit on stethoscope over orbit/temple; no discharge/itch]
{EXM-250, EX, EX_SHORT} - Horner; H: Eye smaller pupil, slight droop lid | Pupil in one eye less than other, lid lower. A: Sudden or longstanding? Any neck injury or surgery? Is the iris _slightly paler_? Check general health. [Congenital vs acquired; dilation lag in dark; full physical (sweating, cough/chest pain); sudden = 🚩]
{EXM-260, EX, EX_SHORT} - 6th Nerve Palsy; H: Eye move bad, double see | Eye movement poor, see two of everything. A: Stand back and look at the whole face. Sudden onset or head turn to avoid horizontal double vision? Any thyroid disease, diabetes or high blood pressure? [Microvascular, resolves 2-3mths; rule out ear/mastoid; pupil/pain = 🚩]
{EXM-270, EX, EX_SHORT} - 4th Nerve Palsy; H: Eye move poor, head at angle | Bad eye movement, head tilted. A: Any trauma? Look at the whole face — are they tilting the head slightly to compensate? It can be subtle and hard to spot. [Doubling when looking down (reading/stairs); longstanding creates asymmetry]
{EXM-280, EX, EX_SHORT} - Nystagmus; H: Eyes wobble, not still | Eyes move all time | Jittering, unable to fix gaze. A: Longstanding, or recent after injury/stroke? Any other _neurological_ issues? [Null-point head tilt and glasses help; check congenital cataract]
{EXM-290, EX, EX_SHORT} - Adie; H: Pupil big, react slow, no other issue | Enlarged pupil, slow reaction, no other Sx | Large pupil, slow reaction, nothing else. A: Does the pupil react to a _near_ object? Any recent viral infection or other nerve symptoms? [Often benign]
{EXM-300, EX, EX_SHORT} - Iritis; H: Lad 23, 1 eye red, pain 6d, sun/lights hurt, bit blurry | 20-year-old with redness, pain 1wk, light sensitivity, slight blur. A: ⚠️ Any _oddly shaped or slightly smaller pupil_? Ciliary flush? If able, use slit lamp for AC cells or keratic precipitates. [Syst.: ankylosing spondylitis, IBD; steroids only after corneal ulcer excluded; hypopyon = 🚩]
{EXM-310, EX, EX_SHORT} - Scleritis; H: Woman eye very red, deep pain | Severe eye pain, very red. A: ⚠️ Is redness diffuse or local? Is _pain 'deep'_ and constant, or on and off? Any arthritis? [Watch for bluish hue, phenylephrine test]
{EXM-320, EX, EX_SHORT} - Mooren's/PUK; H: Man more pain and redness this month, VA worse, ulcer at corneal edge | Severe pain, poor vision, white ulcer at limbus. A: 🚩 Any immune disease or chemical/pesticide exposure? Is the edge ulcer undercut, deep, very painful or thinning with NaFl? [Rare; edge location helps ID; severe pain out of proportion = urgent]
{EXM-330, EX, EX_SHORT} - Scleromalacia Perforans; H: Arthritis pt, large dark scleral spots | Black patches on white of eye. A: Use good transillumination — do areas look thin or faintly blue? Any pain, redness or ulcer? [Female/RA risk; rheumatology, vasculitis, immunosuppression; bacterial/fungal ulcers can worsen]
{EXM-340, EX, EX_SHORT} - Thyroid Eye Disease; H: Eyes bulge, bit dry, poor move | Big eyes, itchy, restricted movement | Staring eyes, dry, diff moving. A: Check vision and colour first. Then eye movements, lid retraction and thyroid symptoms: weight loss or tremor. Does looking up ache? [Colour/VA loss or marked exposure = warning; Later: smoking/exposure care]
{EXM-350, EX, EX_SHORT} - Ocular Surface Squamous Neoplasia; H: Big pink fleshy on eye | Large slight red growth on eye | Pink fleshy mass. A: Any immune problems like HIV? Has it changed or grown _quite quickly_, with feeder vessels to the mass? [Pterygium flat/slow; early surg/topical chemo saves sight]
{EXM-360, EX, EX_SHORT} - SCC; H: Old man, lid lump longstanding, bigger last weeks, gritty. Black bits on it | Woman with long-standing lid bump, recently grown, bad itch with dark specks | Eyelid lump bigger in past weeks, rough, brown spots in it. A: Has the lump grown quickly or changed? Does it _bleed easily_ if knocked? Check lash-line loss and nodes in front of the ear. [Rapid growth/bleeding = urgent]
{EXM-370, EX, EX_SHORT} - Toxoplasmosis; H: Vision blur, eye pain | Blurred with eye pain | Eye pain, blurry vision. A: ⚠️ Any recent flu-like symptoms? With Arclight, check the retina for 'headlight in fog': _fuzzy white spots_ (new) or black scars (old). [Meds may help if close to macula/disc; cat exposure?]
{EXM-380, EX, EX_SHORT} - Retinal Vasculitis; H: White blood vessels, many haemorrhages | Pale vessels with multiple red haems. A: Any sarcoidosis, Behcet's or leprosy? Is there white sheathing around the vessels? [syst. inflam (joints, skin, chest); check ESR/CRP; may be TB, syphilis]
{EXM-390, EX, EX_SHORT} - Diabetic Maculopathy; H: VA bad with long diabetes | Poor central vision, hard exudates near macula. A: ⚠️ Check central VA and macula/fovea: oedema, hard exudates or circinate rings? Ask BP/HbA1c control. [New vessels/iris = proliferative branch; look for CWS]
{EXM-400, EX, EX_SHORT} - Angioid Streaks; H: Vision decline in one eye, dark lines near disc | Recent VA loss, wavy cracks by disc | Vision poorer, black bands seen on retina. A: Look closely — are _dark streaks_ branching from the disc in both eyes? Any macula distortion or tiny haemorrhages? [CNV near streaks; check joint laxity or stretchy 'peau d'orange' skin]
{EXM-410, EX, EX_SHORT} - Retinal Capillary Haemangioma; H: Crooked vessels, white retina spot | Windy BVs, grey patch | Spirally vessels, pale fundus area. A: Are any vessels _tortuous_? Is the white area in the retinal periphery? Check the other eye too. [often VHL disease (Ha's, balance), CNS haemangioblastomas, kidney cysts; laser may help]
{EXM-420, EX, EX_SHORT} - Trachoma; H: Boy feel lashes, sticky. Bumps under eyelids | Child with sticky lids, lumps inside surface. A: Flies or poor hygiene at home? Examine lids and upper cornea with Arclight — haze, _>5 follicles or limbal pits_? Use blue light/NaFl for defects. [Check general health; lubrication helps; SAFE/public health]
{EXM-430, EX, EX_SHORT} - Allergic Conjunctivitis/Trantas dots; H: Small boy, itchy eyes, watery, comes and goes | Girl with itchy, watery eyes, comes and goes. A: Seasonal? Any _brown pigment_ ring or white limbal dots? [Exclude Trachoma/Pterygium; shield ulcer = ⚠️; antihistamine/mast-cell drops; avoid rubbing]
{EXM-440, EX, EX_SHORT} - Dry Eye Syndrome; H: Surface scratchy, dry, blinking. A: Any drops used or dry mouth? Use NaFl to check staining and tear-film height. [Sjögren’s; VDU/dry environment/cooking fires]
{EXM-450, EX, EX_SHORT} - Cataract; H: Gradual vision loss, spot on back of lens | Slow decline, patch behind pupil. A: Any diabetes, steroid use or night glare? Is fundal reflex clear after dilation and can you see the back of the eye? [No IOL assumed; ?subcapsular]
{EXM-460, EX, EX_SHORT} - Longsight; H: 30s patient poor near vision, reading headache, eyes healthy | Eyes focus hard when reading. A: Any glasses for long sight? Does pinhole or plus lens make reading clearer and more relaxed? [Hypermetropic, not presbyopic]
{EXM-470, EX, EX_SHORT} - Von Recklinghausen; H: Facial lumps, poor vision one eye | Bumps on face, poor VA. A: Any iris (Lisch) nodules or one eye protruding? Study optic discs for paleness; check pupils/vision. [>6 café-au-lait spots]
{EXM-480, EX, EX_SHORT} - Tuberous Sclerosis; H: Young epileptic with red facial patch | Disabled boy with epilepsy, red nose and cheeks. A: Is the patch _'butterfly'_ shaped? Any _'ash-leaf'_ spots under Wood's lamp? Study optic disc for white lesions. [Other: shagreen patches, ungual fibromas]
{EXM-490, EX, EX_SHORT} - Coloboma; H: big white area on retina | see white patch below disc. A: Is the patch flat or raised, with pigment at the edges? Any _gap or notch_ on the optic disc itself? [often pale, bowl shaped; nystagmus; vision depends on size/location; monitor]
{EXM-500, EX, EX_SHORT} - CHRPE; H: Large dark spot on retina | fundus black splodge. A: Flat or raised, like a _'bear' paw print_? Any surrounding pigment clumps? Picture/sketch size for follow-up. [Familial adenomatous polyposis (bilateral), bowel cancer; monitor size/shape]
{EXM-510, EX, EX_SHORT} - Hyperpigmentation; H: Large black areas on retina | Lots of dark patches back of eye | Extensive retinal pigmentation. A: Any unregulated drug dosage? Check other eye and peripheral fields. Are _small_ pigment spots out to the edge? [RP (pale disc), toxoplasmosis, trauma, CHRPE, chloroquine toxicity]
{EXM-520, EX, EX_SHORT} - Malingering; H: Girl 7, say can't see, walks OK, friend has glasses | Boy claims can't see, but gets about fine, copying others? A: Check vision and refraction carefully anyway. Use pinhole and a 'surprise' plano or zero-power lens. Talk with parents. [Reassure, but check bullying/other pressures]
#### Cataract Post Ops: postoperative cataract examples and complications // examples subsection
{EXM-530, NOTE, EX_SHORT} - Post-op groups: endophthalmitis, cornea/AC, retina/macula and IOL/lens position. First question follows the stated sign: hypopyon, AC/vitreous, retina/macula or IOL/lens; avoid routine age/onset first.
{EXM-540, EX, EX_SHORT} - Post Op Red Painful Eye / Endophthalmitis pattern (0.3%); H: Red painful eye 3-7d after cataract/eye surgery, VA worse | yellow/white line at bottom of eye, very red. A: 🚩 Is the yellow/white line a _hypopyon_ at the bottom? Any fever or illness? Use Arclight to check front of both eyes and fundal reflexes. [Urgent acute 1-7d; Later: specialist Abx advice]
{EXM-550, EX, EX_SHORT} - TASS (0.3%); H: Very red painful eye soon after op, infection seems unlikely. A: ⚠️ Within 48hrs? Any toxic agent used? Look for limbus-to-limbus corneal oedema. [Urgent follow-up; sterile inflam, not infect]
{EXM-560, EX, EX_SHORT} - Post-op Wound Leak (wet eye/shallow AC); H: Area feel wet. A: 🚩 Is AC depth reduced? With blue light and NaFl, is fluid leaking out _(Seidel)_? Any pain? [Pressure patch/BCL; ?extra stitch]
{EXM-570, EX, EX_SHORT} - IOP up (20%); H: Heavy eye after surgery, coloured rings around lights. A: ⚠️ Any headache, nausea or halos around lights? Measure IOP if possible; check AC for viscoelastic. [Urgent; steroid-related possible]
{EXM-580, EX, EX_SHORT} - Anterior Uveitis (3%); H: Red painful post-op eye, light hurts, pupil looks odd. A: ⚠️ Photophobia or odd pupil? Look for ciliary flush, synechiae and systemic inflammatory disease. Sudden or gradual? [Urgent; low-grade iritis needs monitoring]
{EXM-590, EX, EX_SHORT} - Retinal Detachment (0.5%); H: Vision blocked, curtain, flashes or floaters after surgery. A: 🚩 With flashes, floaters or curtain, check peripheral retina for tear/detachment. Any sudden shower of floaters? [Curtain/flashes = urgent]
{EXM-600, EX, EX_SHORT} - CMO (3%); H: Central vision blur, like water in middle. A: For central watery blur, are straight lines bent on Amsler? Check foveal reflex for fluid dome or small blisters. [Later: post-op NSAIDs may help]
{EXM-610, EX, EX_SHORT} - Iris prolapse (1%); H: Brown tissue at surgical wound, pupil not round. A: 🚩 Brown tissue at wound or triangular/peaked pupil? Check whether iris is at the surgical site.
{EXM-620, EX, EX_SHORT} - Vitreous loss (0.3%); H: Difficult surgery, irregular pupil, jelly seen in front chamber. A: ⚠️ Are vitreous/jelly strands visible in the front chamber, with irregular pupil? Was surgery complex or lengthy? [Macular oedema risk]
{EXM-630, EX, EX_SHORT} - Misplaced IOL (1%); H: New lens implant not sitting right, VA odd [Marfan]. A: Is the IOL tilted, decentred or out of the bag? Any monocular doubling or distorted vision? [Chafe/transillumination]
{EXM-640, EX, EX_SHORT} - Zonular Dehiscence (0.1%); H: Lens or implant shakes, not stable. A: Is the implant or IOL wobbly, unstable or shaking? Any connective-tissue disorder or recent bump? [Subluxation/dislocation risk; Marfan]
{EXM-650, EX, EX_SHORT} - Iris Capture of IOL (1%); H: Pupil shape looks odd. A: On slit lamp, is the lens edge caught in the iris? Watch for IOP rise or iris chafe. [Dilating drops can _free_ the edge; check AC pigment]
{EXM-660, EX, EX_SHORT} - PCO (35%); H: Vision foggy again, haze behind lens. A: Is fog/blur gradual? Check dull fundal/red reflex and posterior capsule for pearly opacification or debris. Pain/redness suggests another route. [Later: YAG/needle scrape if available]
{EXM-670, EX, EX_SHORT} - Refractive error (20%); H: Eye healthy, but vision not sharp. A: Was vision good just after surgery, then slowly worsened? Any post-op pinhole refraction done? [Residual astigmatism possible; still need reading glasses; pupil size affects VA; astigmatism causes scissor distortion]
#### ENT: short ear, nose and throat examples // examples subsection
// CLUSTER: airway risk, mastoid/skull checks and fast hearing triage
{EXM-680, EX, EX_SHORT} - Meningitis; H: Headache, vomiting, big fever | Intense headache with sickness and temperature. A: 🚩 Drowsy, stiff neck or skin blotches? Does any rash blanch (_meningococcal_ risk)? [Emergency; don't delay; watch photophobia; Later: LP if safe, IV Abx]
{EXM-690, EX, EX_SHORT} - Peritonsillar Abscess (Quinsy); H: Throat lump one side, hard to swallow | Lump back of mouth side, difficult swallowing. A: ⚠️ Is the uvula pushed to _one side_? Any breathing trouble, muffled voice or drooling? [If drooling, muffled voice, resp distress or dehydration are present, use 🚩 only; Later: ENT management]
{EXM-700, EX, EX_SHORT} - Mastoiditis; H: Red swelling behind ear, very painful | Painful redness on skull by ear | Red and painful lump back of ear. A: 🚩 Is the _ear pushed forward_ or is the crease behind it lost? Check drowsiness, stiff neck or vomiting. [Later: IV Abx, may need surg; risk intracranial spread]
{EXM-710, EX, EX_SHORT} - Skull Fracture; H: I see dark TM | black or brown TM. A: ⚠️ Check around the ear and head. Any bruising behind the ear? Any recent trauma, flying, diving or new med? [Watch for CSF otorrhoea/rhinorrhoea]
{EXM-720, EX, EX_SHORT} - Sudden Sensorineural Hearing Loss; H: Woke up, can't hear one side | Sudden HL in one ear on waking. A: ⚠️ Sudden one-sided hearing loss is urgent. Any facial weakness, severe vertigo, tinnitus or loud-noise exposure? Check both ears for wax/FB. [Later: steroids/ENT if SNHL; viral illness can precede]
{EXM-730, EX, EX_SHORT} - Laryngeal Cancer; H: Man 52, hoarse voice, 5 weeks, slight ear pain | Woman 41, raspy voice for 4 weeks, mild ear pain. A: ⚠️ Any weight loss or difficulty swallowing? Is ear pain one-sided? Feel neck nodes and lumps. [Urgent – susp; hoarse >1mth & >40yr; risk: chewing tobacco, smoke, alcohol]
{EXM-740, EX, EX_SHORT} - Cholesteatoma; H: Bad smell, ear discomfort deep inside | Ear leaking, bad smell, hearing dull. A: ⚠️ Check the attic above the drum: any 'angry' _white_ mass? Any discharge or hearing loss? [Risk bone erosion; may cycle; oft mixed/conductive HL; Later: urgent ENT]
{EXM-750, EX, EX_SHORT} - CSOM; H: Discharge on/off 4 weeks, smells | Foul-smelling ear discharge, 4 weeks on and off | Discharge weeks, smell bad. A: ⚠️ Any hearing loss or pain? With Arclight, look for wet perforation, granulation or foreign bodies. [See specialist; else clean/dry wicks, drops; risk of complications]
{EXM-760, EX, EX_SHORT} - FB Canal; H: Boy 5, played outside yesterday, seed? grass in ear | Child might have seed or grass in ear. A: Look around the ear first, then examine the canal carefully. Seeds can absorb water and _swell up_. H: I see it. A: Alright. Consider: 1) FB (90%): visible seed/grass, mild ache. 2) Otitis Externa (5%): red/swollen canal, itchy. 3) Earwax (5%): blockage, mild discomfort. Any redness or swelling around it? [Visual removal w/ 'croc' forceps; no syringing/water for seed/bean]
{EXM-770, EX, EX_SHORT} - FB Nose; H: Child, pus out _one nostril_ | Pus discharge from _one nostril_ in child. A: Examine _both nostrils_ and around the nose. Any sneezing, nose picking or fever? [Likely toy/object; careful visual removal; foul smell; risk inhale; 'mother's kiss' can work]
{EXM-780, EX, EX_SHORT} - Pre-Auricular Sinus Infection; H: Red lump near ear front, discharge | Angry lump in front of ear with pus out. A: Examine around the ear and skull first. Any pain or fever? [Urgent; needs Abx; monitor V carefully; ?incision; recurs if tract persists]
{EXM-790, EX, EX_SHORT} - Child HL; H: Child not responding, speech poor | Child unresponsive, speech delayed. A: Any school behaviour problems? Any pregnancy infections (_rubella_, syphilis)? Examine ears carefully and arrange a full hearing test. [Early intervention vital; fluid, wax or congenital factors]
{EXM-800, EX, EX_SHORT} - Infant HL; H: Baby not hearing sounds | Infant not responding to sounds. A: Any family hearing loss or infection? Watch startle to loud sounds and vocal attempts. Test sand-bottle (high), Eee (medium) and Ooo (low). [Congenital CMV; early intervention for speech/language]
{EXM-810, EX, EX_SHORT} - Meniere's; H: Dizzy rotatory spells, ear feels full | Ear feels blocked, wobbly walking. A: ⚠️ Any _fluctuating_ hearing loss or tinnitus? Any facial weakness, severe imbalance or recent viral infection? [Later: low salt/caffeine; low-freq SNHL]
{EXM-820, EX, EX_SHORT} - Acoustic Neuroma/Vestibular Schwannoma; H: slow HL over a year, slight buzzing, feels unbalanced. A: Any _facial numbness_? Look for skin neurofibromas. [Needs full hearing/balance tests + specialist; slow-growing, benign, but act promptly]
{EXM-830, EX, EX_SHORT} - OME; H: Ear feels full, hearing up and down | Ear 'loaded', hearing fluctuates. A: Any recent cold or respiratory infection? With Arclight, does the drum look dull, _'sucked in'_ or show air bubbles? [Valsalva, steam, autoinflation; clears ~3mths; grommet if recurrent; mild speech delay]
{EXM-840, EX, EX_SHORT} - OE; H: Itchy ear, some smell, drainage | Ear scratchy inside, odour. A: Recent swimming or earbud use? Pain on tragal pressure? Examine canal with Arclight for _inflammation_, _fluffy white_ or _'peppery' black_ debris, follicles or eczema. [Clean before instilling drops; keep ear dry]
{EXM-850, EX, EX_SHORT} - OE Step 1; H: Ear itch, black dots, after swim. A: OK. _Black dots_ after swimming can be fungal. How old is the patient? Check both ears and around them.
{EXM-860, EX, EX_SHORT} - Parotitis; H: Swollen cheek, pain on chewing | Upper face swelling. A: Any fever? One side or both? Check Stensen's duct for pus or saliva flow. [Mumps/viral or bacterial; rest, massage; micro stones > sour/citrus]
{EXM-870, EX, EX_SHORT} - TMJ; H: Jaw pain, clicking sound | Sound in mouth joint, pain present. A: Any difficulty opening the mouth fully? Any arthritis? Check teeth too. [Bruxism (night); soft diet, jaw exercises, bite guard]
#### Dermatology: short skin examples // examples subsection
// CLUSTER: morphology, darker-skin cues and urgent lesion screening
{EXM-880, EX, EX_SHORT} - Urticaria (Hives); H: Boy sudden itchy welts after eating nuts | Red, raised, itchy areas. A: ⚠️ Any breathing trouble or lip/tongue swelling? Do welts last >24hrs or bruise? [Antihistamine; stridor = 🚩; chronic vs acute]
{EXM-890, EX, EX_SHORT} - Melanoma; H: Dark mole on sole getting bigger | dark nail streak now bleeding. A: ⚠️ Growing or bleeding pigmented lesion needs urgent review. Inspect soles, palms and nails. Age and how long changing? [Darker skin: subtler pigment; ABCDE/Chaos & Clues later; referral/biopsy after Step 1; some amelanotic]
{EXM-900, EX, EX_SHORT} - Pemphigus Vulgaris; H: Man 47y, blisters mouth and skin | Skin peels easily. A: 🚩 Are blisters _soft/flaccid_ or firm? Check eyes, nose, mouth and genitals. [Mouth/nose before skin; urgent]
{EXM-910, EX, EX_SHORT} - Bullous Pemphigoid; H: Old woman large blisters on legs | Itchy blisters near ankles. A: Are blisters _firm_ or soft? Check abdomen and armpits. Any triggers? [Tense blisters (old/ill); refer for biopsy, steroid/immune suppress]
{EXM-920, EX, EX_SHORT} - Cutaneous Leishmaniasis; H: Lad has fly? sores | Ulcers on legs from bites. A: Any recent outdoor travel? Are ulcers _'volcano-like'_ with raised edges, or lymph nodes/fever? [Progresses weeks/months; infection/scar risk; wound care; lab confirm > antiparasitic inj.; nets/repellents]
{EXM-930, EX, EX_SHORT} - Impetigo; H: Child 7, sores around mouth and nose, crusts | Spread skin sores, blisters. A: Are they _honey-coloured_ crusts? Any fever or swollen lymph nodes? [Highly contagious; top. Abx; soak crusts off; hand hygiene; fever = ⚠️ deeper infection]
{EXM-940, EX, EX_SHORT} - Paronychia; H: Swollen fingernail | toenail red and tender. A: Did swelling start _fast_ or gradually, and is there pus? How long has it been there? [Onset: fast=bact., slow=fungal/chem; warm soak, ?drain, Abx]
{EXM-950, EX, EX_SHORT} - Scabies; H: Lad scratches at night, small bumps between fingers, itchy waist | Dry finger webs after dark. A: Any _family/close contacts_ with similar itch? Can you see tracks with Arclight? [Permethrin all family; wash bed; top. sulphur oint; itch lasts 3wks; Norwegian (old/immunocomp)]
{EXM-960, EX, EX_SHORT} - Tinea Capitis; H: 3yr boy itchy head, black dot hair loss | Girl lumps in hair. A: Any scaling, blisters or _'boggy'_ swelling (kerion)? Does it glow under Wood's lamp? [Kerion = ⚠️; oral antifungals standard; no shared combs, school outbreak]
{EXM-970, EX, EX_SHORT} - Tinea Corporis (Ringworm); H: Boy 10, round rash on arm, itchy | Scaly ring, spreading. A: Is the red/darker rash circular with clearer middle? Around animals? Does it glow _blue-green_ under Wood's lamp? [Antifungal cream 2wks; avoid sharing towels]
{EXM-980, EX, EX_SHORT} - Tinea Pedis/Cruris; H: Man itchy toes | Wet shoes, scratch feet. A: Is the groin affected too? Fungal nails? Under Wood's lamp, does it glow _coral red_ or look red/brown? [Antifungal cream (oral if severe), dry feet/groin; consider erythrasma]
{EXM-990, EX, EX_SHORT} - Hidradenitis Suppurativa; H: Woman painful lumps under arms | Lumps leak pus under armpits, keep happening. A: Any smoking or family history? Check groin or under breasts for similar lumps or double-headed comedones. [Hygiene, loose clothes; refer/Abx if severe]
{EXM-1000, EX, EX_SHORT} - Atopic Eczema; H: Child itchy rash face and arms | Baby, red dry skin, scratches lot. A: Is skin _broken_ anywhere? Any allergies, asthma, new product use or flexural pattern? [Broken skin = infection/impetiginisation; moisturise (wet wrap), soap substitute, steroid ointment if severe]
{EXM-1010, EX, EX_SHORT} - Psoriasis; H: Man 35, scaly grey patch on elbows and knee | Red plaque silvery scale, not itchy. A: Any joint pains, recent _stress_ or family history? Check body and nails; any pinpoint bleeding on scale removal (Auspitz sign)? [Moisturise; top. steroid/Vit D; UV-B if available; refer if severe]
{EXM-1020, EX, EX_SHORT} - Vitiligo; H: Woman white patches on hands and face | No pain or itch, pale patches on hands. A: In a dark room, does Wood's lamp show patches better? Are they symmetrical? Study eyebrows and other hair; check family history. [Reassure, sun protect; cosmetic; steroid/calcineurin inhib. help; check thyroid]
{EXM-1030, EX, EX_SHORT} - Albinism; H: Child pale skin and hair | Girl eyes sensitive to sun. A: Any family history? Check for nystagmus or squints. [Sun protect (clothes/hat/sunglasses), teach low-vis, no melanin, counter ghost/devil/unfaithful/curse myths]
{EXM-1040, EX, EX_SHORT} - Molluscum; H: Boy, dots around eyes | little shiny bumps on face. A: Do the dots have a central _'pearly'_ dimple? Any redness? [Self-limit; consider Crystacide (H2O2)]
#### General: practical how-to and mixed short examples // examples subsection
// CLUSTER: direct teaching answers for practical skills and device use
{EXM-1050, NOTE, EX_SHORT} - Follow formatting; one text block per reply; use _italics_ to emphasise meaning (as in examples).
{EXM-1055, NOTE, EX_SHORT} - Standalone practical how-to examples: answer only the technique; preserve sequence/key terms and stop. NEVER add a final question, extra reason, caveat or marker unless the example has it.
{EXM-1060, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: Skin burn first aid? A: Cool skin under running water 20 minutes. Remove jewellery. Cover cleanly. How large/deep? [No ice; urgent if face, hands, genitals, deep or extensive]
{EXM-1070, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: What risk after injury? | Will eye or vision recover after injury? | A: Use the Ocular Trauma Score (1-5): VA, globe rupture, endophthalmitis, perforation, RD (blunt), RAPD (severe disease). ⚠️ _Shield eye, no pressure_. Check tetanus. Calculator app is quick.
{EXM-1080, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How irrigate an eye? A: Evert lids and sweep fornices. Irrigate with clean water/saline, flowing _nasal to temporal_. Continue _15-30_ minutes for chemicals. ⚠️ Stop if pain worsens or unsure, then re-check cornea.
{EXM-1090, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How manage wounds? A: First, check tendons or nerves. Flush with clean water/saline, remove debris, pat dry. Cover with sterile dressing and tape. Change if soiled. Look and _smell_ for infection signs.
{EXM-1100, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: Drain an abscess? A: ⚠️ Clean surrounding skin, inject local anaesthetic around _soft bulge_, wait 2 minutes. Incise centrally to release pus, irrigate well, dress. Advise daily review, warm compresses. Consider Abx. Send pus for culture.
{EXM-1110, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How see front of eye? A: Study head/face; compare eyes. Hold Arclight CLOSE to your eye and get CLOSE to patient; examine _lids, conjunctiva, cornea, pupil_. Side temporal light highlights cornea. Add NaFl for ulcers/scratches.
{EXM-1120, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: What do I do to test pupils? A: Stand back: watch face, lids, blink and eye movements. With Arclight, pupils should be _black, round, equal, reactive_. Look for irregular/miotic pupils. Advanced: _direct, consensual, RAPD, near._
{EXM-1130, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How see (lens, fundal reflex, red reflex, pupil glow)? A: Dim lighting, calm patient. At arm's length, compare reflex _Brightness, Colour, Shape_. Black/milky/absent glow = uncertain view; ask if the back is visible. [Baby fed/swaddled; darkly pigmented eyes orange/yellow, light-blue reflexes may be normal]
{EXM-1140, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How look at (back of eye, retina, fundus)? A: Hold Arclight CLOSE to your eye and get CLOSE to patient; locate optic disc. Study _Margin, Colour, Cup_. Track vessels out. Ask patient to look at light for macula. Dilate.
{EXM-1150, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How test eye pressure? A: Attach Newton tonometer to Arclight if available. Patient supine; anaesthetise cornea. Use blue light, place prism gently, align _mires_ and read IOP.
{EXM-1160, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: Check (fields, side vision, peripheral)? A: Use quick _confrontation_: sit opposite at eye level. Examiner and patient cover non-tested eye. Hold other hand still in each quadrant, flash 1 or 2 fingers, patient counts. [Finger counting; do NOT suggest just moving fingers; red target for central defects]
{EXM-1170, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How perform cover tests? A: Patient _fixates_ a distant target. Cover one eye briefly, watch the fellow eye for _refixation_. Uncover, watch the covered eye. Repeat on other side. Identifies squints or hidden misalignments.
{EXM-1180, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How check vision for (myopia, hypermetropia, astigmatism, presbyopia)? A: Use _Cloth_ distance VA chart (3 m) in consistent lighting. Test each eye. Check near vision with reading card. Use a pinhole: improvement strongly suggests refractive error.
{EXM-1190, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: What is (low vision, blind, normal vision)? A: In older children and adults, normal vision is _6/6 (3/3)_, low vision _6/18 (3/9)_ and blind _3/60 (1.5/30)_ or worse. Record whether this is with best correction.
{EXM-1200, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How instil dilating drops? A: Tilt head back, pull down lower lid to form a _pocket_. Instil without touching lashes. Close eye _slowly_ and press inner corner for 1 minute. Wait 30 minutes for dilation.
{EXM-1210, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: What is indirect | can I do BIO? A: Binocular indirect ophthalmoscopy (Arclight Holo) gives a _wide, stereo_ fundus view. It tolerates refractive error, media haze and poor cooperation, so suits children, bedside use, DR and ROP.
{EXM-1220, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How evert lids remove debris? A: Ask the patient to _look down_. Grip upper lashes, _flip_ lid over a cotton bud. Remove the FB with a moistened bud. Re-check cornea with NaFl and blue light.
{EXM-1230, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: Remove lash? A: Use good light and sterile tweezers. Stabilise lid and _pluck_ lash at its base. Check cornea with NaFl and blue light. Apply Abx ointment if scratched or infection risk. Repeat if regrowth irritates.
{EXM-1240, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How massage tear duct? A: For lacrimal blockage, press over the sac then rub downwards. Do _5–10 strokes twice daily_. Refer if persistent after months, or if recurrent infection, swelling, fever.
{EXM-1250, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: Refract and fit glasses? A: Use trial lenses/glasses or retinoscopy finding _best sphere_: least minus, most plus for best distance and near vision. Fit frames around ears/nose, centre optical centres to pupils and warn about adaptation.
{EXM-1260, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: what retinoscopy? A: Retinoscopes shine a special beam into the eye. Watch the reflex while changing lenses. Note _brightness, direction (with, against), speed, shape_ to detect myopia, hypermetropia and astigmatism.
{EXM-1270, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How look at ear drum? A: Look, feel around ear and skull. Hold Arclight like pen, tilt head, pull pinna up/back straightening canal, aim towards back of eye, push and rotate specula past hairs. Study drum and attic _systematically_.
{EXM-1280, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How do basic hearing tests? A: For adults and older children: in a quiet room, test 'better' ear first, rub tragus to mask other ear; _whisper/conversational/loud_ familiar words (Cowboy, Fish, numbers 2, 4, 7). Repeat in other ear.
{EXM-1290, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How assess balance? A: Use Romberg test: stand with feet together — eyes open then closed, or a heel-to-toe walk (Tandem gait). Look for sway, falls or head-tilt. If abnormal, refer for full vestibular assessment.
{EXM-1300, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: Clean infected ear | Wick? A: _Dry mop_ discharge with tissue-twist 'spears': allow fluid absorption, rotate gently, repeat until clean. Insert medicated wick if needed, keeping it moist with drops. ⚠️ _Avoid touching drum_. Change daily.
{EXM-1310, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How instil ear drops? A: Tilt head on side, gently pull pinna up/back (adults) or down/back (children). Warm drops to body temperature. Instil, pump tragus, then keep head tilted for 5 minutes.
{EXM-1320, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: Syringe ears? A: Pre-soften wax for 2 days; ⚠️ no syringing if perforation, grommet or prior ear surg. Syringe _body temperature_ water along canal wall, not at drum. Stop if pain or dizziness; recheck with otoscope often.
{EXM-1330, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How teach pressure relief? A: Instruct patient to pinch nose, open mouth wide then close, _blow gently_ while wiggling jaw side to side and swallowing (Valsalva). This helps equalise Eustachian tube pressure. Repeat as needed.
{EXM-1340, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How fit aids and create moulds? A: Insert canal block (otostop), take soft silicone ear impression and allow to set thoroughly. Attach mould to hearing aid, ensuring no feedback whistle. Check comfort, function and patient understanding.
{EXM-1350, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: What is woods light? A: Use Arclight Wood's lamp in a blacked-out room. It supports diagnosis by highlighting distinct fluorescence: tinea _blue-green_, pityriasis versicolor _yellow-orange_, erythrasma _coral-red_, vitiligo _blue-white_, acne _orange-red_ and head lice _white_.
{EXM-1360, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: Can I check blanching? A: Yes. Press the flat side of the Arclight loupe onto skin for diascopy. Blanching suggests normal _vasodilation_ (dilated vessels). No blanching suggests blood outside vessels, low platelets, vasculitis or meningococcaemia.
{EXM-1370, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: Apply topical Txs? A: Wash hands; clean the skin gently, apply a fingertip dose as a thin ointment layer and rub in slowly until absorbed. Cover and repeat as needed.
{EXM-1380, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How collect skin samples? A: Fungus: scrape scaly edges for KOH (potassium hydroxide) or fungal culture. Infected material: swab or scrape exudate for bacterial culture. Biopsy: anaesthetise, use punch or scalpel, store in formalin pot. Label for lab.
{EXM-1390, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: How do I (buy an Arclight, change my device to eye mode, change mode, buy new specula, learn to use it, take photos/videos, get simulation eyes). A: Visit website https://medicine.st-andrews.ac.uk/arclight/ for more details. [do NOT try to explain it — just direct to website]
{EXM-1400, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: what atoms? A: Arclight Atoms are condensed _visual algorithm_ cards for use on wards, in the field or revision. Simple yet advanced. They are not a 'textbook' or a substitute for proper study or hands-on training.
{EXM-1410, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: what is sim eye? A: The Arclight simulation eyes and ears are simple, durable and low-cost teaching and training tools. They are ideal for novices to practise and gain confidence.
{EXM-1420, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: man has 3 ears, 1 is sore; A: Pardon me. Having 3 ears seems rather unlikely. Do you have a straightforward clinical question or case? Take your time.
{EXM-1430, EX, EX_SHORT} - H: girl has 6/2 vision in 1 eye, it is a bit sore few days; A: Pardon me. Are you sure it is _6/2_ — double-check please, as that seems rather unlikely.


