{MEM-040, RED, MEM_RED} - Chemical eye splash/burn or lime/cement dust: first reply emergency: irrigate water/saline now 30min. Ask vision + one/both eyes; sweep lids/fornices for retained particles. Later: pH 7; limbal blanching.
{MEM-050, RED, MEM_RED} - Penetrating FB: high-speed; shield NOT pad; urgent (Seidel).
{MEM-060, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Trauma (Eye): When/how?; blunt/sharp?; pupil size/shape; torn/out/not right?; look hyphaema.
{MEM-070, LIST, MEM_EYE} - Ocular Trauma Score (1-5): VA, Globe Rupt, Endoph, Perforate, RD (blunt), RAPD (sev. disease).
{MEM-080, RED, MEM_RED} - Child swollen-shut febrile lid or restricted EOM: orbital danger; ask one/both eyes, proptosis, drowsiness and vision/EOM. Later: hospital.
{MEM-090, RED, MEM_RED} - Preseptal vs Orbital Cellulitis: red swollen lid with VA, EOM and proptosis normal = preseptal; fever, EOM pain/restriction, proptosis or VA down = orbital. Later: hospital Abx.
{MEM-100, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Red Eye(s): Unilateral susp = serious (ulcer, uveitis, acute glaucoma); Watery, yellow/green, pain/itch/grit; local/all-round red?
{MEM-110, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Corneal Ulcers: Sx, Stain, Site (mid/periph), Shape, SIZE (mm); sterilise+heal; central > treat aggressive.
{MEM-120, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Ulcer Types: Site first. Peripheral/limbal or undercut ulcer -> Mooren's/PUK cues: very painful, immune disease, chemical/pesticide, thinning. Central/typical bacterial -> size, hypopyon, trauma or recent surgery. Fungal -> raised feather/jagged, farm/veg. Viral -> dendritic/branching stain, corneal sense loss; NO steroid. Vernal -> upper shield.
{MEM-126, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Red painful/cloudy eye + steroid request: corneal ulcer risk; check cornea/fluorescein/ulcer before treatment.
{MEM-125, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Hypopyon/yellow-white line at bottom: ask whether line is hypopyon/pus or blood before surgery/trauma/vision.
{MEM-130, RED, MEM_RED} - AACG/fixed dilated pupil/halos: severe red-eye danger; ask vision, halos/N/V, fixed pupil and corneal haze. Later: IOP/angles, analgesia, Diamox + Pilocarpine.
{MEM-140, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Iritis: red limbus/ciliary flush; photophobia; small/irreg pupil; steroid unsafe until corneal ulcer excluded; when steroid requested, check ciliary flush and fluorescein staining/ulcer together.
{MEM-145, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Corneal clouding + painful red eye: red flag; ask vision, contact lens/trauma, fluorescein staining/ulcer or hypopyon.
{MEM-150, RED, MEM_RED} - New Diplopia: urgent; sudden 3rd/6th CNP > urgent refer; subtle 4th > soon refer.
{MEM-160, RED, MEM_RED} - Carotid-Cavernous Fistula: pulsatile red eye/proptosis, corkscrew vessels, bruit/'whoosh', diplopia/ptosis; often post-trauma; Urgent.
