{MEM-210, RED, MEM_RED} - Amaurosis Fugax: transient one-eye/monocular blackout = red flag; ask BP, bruits, weakness and GCA symptoms.
{MEM-220, LIST, MEM_EYE} - 4 Optic Discs: ALWAYS first study both discs: Margin/Colour/Cup & ?cupping; then classify: a) NORMAL; b) SWOLLEN: echo swollen disc, ask HA/vomit/diplopia/BP; bilat norm VA/pupil = Papilloedema; unilat VA down+slug pupil+EOM pain = Optic Neuritis; c) NEW-VESSELS = diabetic; d) PALE/WHITE: red if very poor VA with RAPD/reduced pupil response, sudden VA loss or GCA symptoms; warning if reduced VA/sluggish pupil without those; d1) cup close, older, slug pupil, good cent VA, poor side VA = glaucoma; d2) 1 pale = ON (?meningioma/pituitary, check field); d3) both v.pale + poor VA = toxic ON, ask medicines/toxins-at-work; d4) young + temp pallor + poor central VA + poor diet/smoke/alcohol = nutrition ON; d5) sudden VA loss, pale disc+few haem+>50yr = AION.
{MEM-230, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Sudden central VA loss + healthy disc: macula first; ask Amsler/distortion, macula appearance and pupil.
{MEM-240, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Retinal Vascular Occlusion: CRVO (blood & thunder), 100-day glaucoma (iris). CRAO = emergency stroke/eye review; check bruits/GCA.
{MEM-250, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - DR (T1 >15y, T2 >5y): Sleep/eat/move/think well; no alcohol/smoke; glycaemic control. Monitor BP/lipid/HbA1c. Tx: aVEGF, laser. Background > monitor. Non-Prolif DR (NPDR): MA, D/B, CWS, VB > monitor reg (BP, kidney, nerve, feet). Prolif DR (PDR): NVD/E, VH > Urgent (RD); check iris for new vessels. Maculopathy: HE > monitor. Foveopathy: HE+oedema, cent VA loss > Urgent. Pathophys: BV glucose sens > narrow/low flow; Wall fail > aneurysm/haem; Neuron fail > CWS; BV/muscle fail > inflam fluid/lipid oedema; Low O2/fragile new BV > bleed, fibrosis, detach; men underDx.
{MEM-260, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Open Angle Glaucoma (OAG): ALWAYS ask disc cup?; refer soon. Check: VA, Pupil (slug), Disc, IOP (if poss), Field. Each test powerful combined. Poor side or night vision helps. Lifelong drops (educate)/Laser/Surg. Key signs: big cup, thin rim, notch (esp sm disc). Risks: disc, IOP, age, race, FHx, myopia, DM/BP, thin cornea.
{MEM-270, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - AMD: Amsler each eye; nav/face/text; 85% dry/15% wet; good illum+LVA; >Charles Bonnet; bright light, magnifier, green food.
{MEM-280, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Toxoplasmosis: 'headlight in fog' active white retinitis near old pigmented scar; ask cats/flu-like illness; treat if macula/disc threatened.
