{MEM-310, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Cataracts: Adv: white/grey, not red/sore; adult IOL surg if VA poor + no RAPD + good light direction (>50yr); ALWAYS refer baby/child suspect cataract. Congenital: usually both eyes, stops visual development (nystagmus); older child/YA if 1 eye > leave alone; if able check contrast sensitivity/amblyopia. Traumatic too. Age-rel. Types: Nuclear (yellow/brown, blur); Cortical (spokes, blur + glare); Subcapsular (patch, glare). Early > ?malnutrition/steroid overuse. Tx: emphasise low-cost Govt/NGO surg; early child Tx reduces amblyopia; reduce fall/injury risk.
{MEM-320, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Baby Vision (>3mth): Arm's-length face-fix.
{MEM-325, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Child white/grey pupil/reflex/lens or poor fix-follow: red marker; ask fundal/red reflex, both eyes and squint/fix-follow. Big cloudy photophobic infant eyes use congenital glaucoma cues.
{MEM-330, DO, MEM_EYE} - Cycloplegic Rx: Dim room; give full Rx (anisometropia >4D high risk yet often little benefit); treat <8yr; patch 'good' eye; Adv: gaze pos, corneal light, cover/alt-cover, epicanthus.
{MEM-340, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Cerebral VI (CVI): 3 Cat: CVI=Eyes (no smile/reach, holds close, rove eye, startle); CVI>Eyes (stare light, noisy/clutter diff); Eyes>CVI (fast wobbly eye, poke eye; birth, epilepsy, trauma/drug); bright toy/colour; often delay motor/speech.
{MEM-350, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Adolescent Vision Loss (Healthy Eye): ?Functional, stress.
{MEM-360, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Post-op persistent inflammation + raised IOP: inspect AC for retained cortical fragments; washout may be needed.
{MEM-370, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Post-op cornea: fine folds/early oedema may settle with lubrication and rest; persistent haze or _bullae_ -> refer.
{MEM-375, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Fundal reflex/pupil glow: black, milky or absent glow = uncertain view/media opacity; compare Brightness/Colour/Shape and ask if back visible before history.
// CLUSTER: baseline vision language, refraction clues and routine eye-tool interpretation
{MEM-380, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Vision/Refraction Basics: Dist/Near VA first; pinhole improve = uncorrect refract error; Poor VA+NO pinhole improve = look back of eye; 6/18 low vis, 3/60 blind. DV poor+NV good = Myopia (pinhole); good light read, outdoor activ. DV+NV poor/focus <40yr = Hypermetropia (converg. effort reveal). Presbyopia >40yr; DO NOT say starts early; tilt page, bright light; 'stronger' add often = hidden hyperopia. Add guide: 40 +0.75; 50 +1.50; 60 +2.00; 70 +2.50; 80 +2.75; IOL +3.00.
{MEM-390, TERM, MEM_EYE} - Fundal reflex = pupil glow from fundus at arm's length with Arclight; prefer to red reflex (not always red; varies with pigmentation/optics); suggests, not confirms, visible back of eye; null/milky/black likely unseen.
{MEM-400, LIST, MEM_EYE} - NaFl+Arclight Blue: FB, CL, trauma/chem, dry, worsening red blur, keratitis/ulcer (check white patch, size and hypopyon), trachoma.
{MEM-410, DO, MEM_EYE} - Photos/Videos: Ideal for Px, 2nd opinion, baseline.
{MEM-420, DO, MEM_EYE} - Glasses: Robust, attract, fit well, no press mark; cheap/local; protect farmer/welder; clean soft cloth (no detergent).
// CLUSTER: lids, conjunctiva and common anterior-segment follow-up rules
{MEM-430, RED, MEM_RED} - Lid Lesion (Speed/Bleed): ask how long it has changed; judge fast as days/weeks and slow as months/years; ask bleeding. BCC: 90%, lower lid, slow > refer soon. SCC: 5%, Urgent, fast, 'angry', spread (Doubt, cut out!). Stye/BCC same loc.
{MEM-440, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Thyroid Eye Disease: lid retraction/stare, proptosis, dry exposure, restricted EOM; ask vision/colour loss, movement and thyroid Sx/smoking; no marker unless colour/VA loss or marked exposure.
{MEM-450, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Conjunctivitis: Usual self-limit (wash hands/towels); lubes help. Allergic disease usually bilateral, itchy. Severe unilateral pain/photophobia = urgent. Child Allergic: itchy, limbal pigment, seasonal, Trantas dots. Newborn Gonococcal = Urgent (perf risk); check ears.
{MEM-460, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Lids: blepharitis = itchy/sticky morning lids, crust/collarettes, lash loss/lid margin; chalazion = lid lump. Ask lids/lashes first and whether lump is recurrent, severe or painful. Later warm compress; doxy if severe/recur. Molluscum (pearly lid nodule, chronic conjunctivitis; check body/family; USE Crystacide and/or antiviral; immunodef adult).
{MEM-470, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Sub-Conj Haemorrhage: Sector/total; check BP; resolves <2wk.
{MEM-480, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Dermoid: Orbital/limbal; unless non-mobile/large/growing/affect vision > leave alone; monitor.
{MEM-490, LIST, MEM_EYE} - Dystrophies: Fuchs, Lattice, Vortex; FHx.
### LMIC / Tropical Ophthalmology: eye disease, nutrition and endemic conditions // memory subsection
// CLUSTER: nutrition, endemic infection and avoidable blindness causes
{MEM-500, RED, MEM_RED} - Baby/infant sticky or pus eye: if the sclera is white and quiet, ask fever, lid swelling, red eye and cloudy cornea; only white pupil/reflex triggers white-pupil concern.
{MEM-510, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Xerophthalmia: underfed/measles/diarrhoea; night blind, dry/Bitot, corneal xerosis/ulcer; Vit A lifesaving.
{MEM-520, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Measles eye Cx: keratitis, corneal ulcer/scar, blindness; Vit A crucial.
{MEM-530, RED, MEM_RED} - HIV/AIDS eye: CMV retinitis ('pizza pie' fundus, floaters, VA loss = urgent); CWS; Kaposi lid/conj; HZO.
{MEM-540, RED, MEM_RED} - ROP (Retinopathy of Prematurity): preterm <2kg/4.4lb, ~6wk early, O2; ask paired cues: gestation/birth weight/O2 + follows faces/smiles; check fundal reflex/white patches. Later: BIO, laser/aVEGF.
{MEM-550, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Trachoma/trichiasis: upper-lid scars/lashes touching cornea -> warning marker if cloudy cornea or reduced sight; check both eyes, vision, corneal opacity and NaFl defects. Later: TT surgery/SAFE.
{MEM-555, CHECK, MEMORY} - Myths/folk practices: no marker for proposed practice only; mark only actual injury/exposure or danger signs; use "I am quite certain", "It would be ill-advised" or "I must insist".
{MEM-560, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Traditional/harmful eye remedies: only address if a remedy, herb, chemical, traditional practice or home drop is mentioned. Ask what was used; explain risk briefly; stop it and offer safer care.
{MEM-570, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - River blindness/oncho: river village + itchy thick/leopard skin + cloudy corneal scars -> ask blackfly exposure, vision and skin findings. Later: local ivermectin rules.
{MEM-575, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Eye worm: moving worm on eye after fly exposure = warning; ask location/visibility plus redness, cornea and vision. No extraction instructions first.
{MEM-580, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - Leprosy eye: lagophthalmos/corneal anaesthesia; first ask corneal redness, clouding/white patch, ulcer or VA loss. Warning unless corneal damage/VA loss; later protect/lubricate.
{MEM-590, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - TB eye: recurrent red eye + corneal nodules/phlyctenules or uveitis/choroiditis/vasculitis = warning; ask cough, fever, weight loss and TB contact. No regimen dosing.
{MEM-600, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - VKC: severe allergy (hot/dry climate, young M); intense itch, ropy discharge, cobblestones (upper tarsus), shield ulcer.
{MEM-610, CHECK, MEM_EYE} - EHC/outbreak red eye: watery + photophobia/pain +/- blood patches; ask spread/contacts and vision/cornea danger; no antibiotic launch.

### ENT: ear, nose and throat heuristics // memory subsection
// NOTE: ENT memory emphasises exam order, dangerous spread patterns and hearing shortcuts
// CLUSTER: exam order, intracranial spread risks and head-and-neck escalation triggers
{MEM-620, DO, MEM_ENT} - ENT Hx/Exam: ALWAYS examine/palpate ear, TMJ, mastoid, skull; assess neuralgia, skin lesion, lymph node; examine BOTH ears, nose, throat; check temp. Otoscopy: inspect 'better' ear 1st; calm pt (baby fed/swaddled); hold like pen; pull pinna up/back (infant down/back); aim speculum to back of eye, past hair; study TM (grey/pink, landmarks) & attic; note perforation, retraction, effusion.
{MEM-630, RED, MEM_RED} - Red warm painful pinna: ask lobule spared, cartilage swelling, trauma/piercing and fever. Post-auricular swelling, pushed-forward ear, very unwell or stiff neck = red.
{MEM-640, RED, MEM_RED} - Skull fracture/haemotympanum: blue/dark TM or Battle's sign after trauma; ?CSF otorrhoea/rhinorrhoea = emergency.
{MEM-650, RED, MEM_RED} - Diabetic severe ear pain + facial weakness: red flag; check facial nerve, canal swelling/granulation, discharge and fever. Later: malignant OE/skull-base infection, painkiller, IV Abx.
{MEM-660, RED, MEM_RED} - Cholesteatoma: Check attic first; echo 'angry' white mass/smell above drum, bad discharge or hearing loss before skull-danger checks. Later: urgent ENT (prevent bone erosion/Cx).
{MEM-670, RED, MEM_RED} - Sudden HL ('gone deaf'): warning marker unless wax/FB is visible in canal and no facial weakness, severe vertigo, tinnitus or loud-noise exposure; if wax/FB visible, ask whether it blocks canal and check both ears without marker. If hearing remains poor after clearing, treat as sudden HL.
{MEM-675, RED, MEM_RED} - Sudden HL with severe vertigo, vomiting or cannot walk: red flag; ask face, speech, weakness or vision.
{MEM-680, RED, MEM_RED} - Facial Nerve Palsy: Exclude OM, parotid tumour; Urgent; ?Ramsay Hunt.
{MEM-690, DO, MEM_ENT} - Bell's Palsy: Check BP, glucose; steroid <72hr may help; protect eye (tape shut).
{MEM-700, RED, MEM_RED} - Hoarse >1mth: try indirect mirror; ?acid reflux, chronic throat clearing; Susp laryngeal CA (esp smoker M); Urgent.
{MEM-710, RED, MEM_RED} - Neck mass/lymph nodes >2-3wks: check fixed/matted/fluctuant nodes, mouth/throat source and TB/HIV/weight loss; tests/biopsy later.
{MEM-720, RED, MEM_RED} - Oral white patch/leukoplakia: non-wipe/scrape + betel/tobacco are key; ask hard/bleeding/persistent; biopsy later.
{MEM-730, RED, MEM_RED} - Fungal sinusitis: invasive (DM/immunocomp), black necrotic tissue; ask facial/orbital spread first; emergency.
{MEM-740, RED, MEM_RED} - Tonsillitis/Quinsy: ask uvula deviation and breathing first; hot potato voice, trismus; urgent if drooling, muffled voice, respiratory distress or dehydration; ENT management later.
{MEM-750, RED, MEM_RED} - Stridor (infant): ?laryngomalacia; monitor breathing/cyanosis; cyanosis/distress = emergency.
{MEM-760, RED, MEM_RED} - Swollen Cheek: ?Dental abscess; palpate gum for fluctuance ('boggy'); Later: dental/ENT drainage + Abx.
{MEM-770, RED, MEM_RED} - Ear Canal Tumour: Unusual gran. tissue, persist. bleed, mass; biopsy, spec. Tx.
{MEM-780, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - Darker skin: cyanosis check blue lips, under tongue, nail beds; pallor oral mucosa/conjunctiva (anaemia); tonsillitis focus swelling/exudate; nasal congestion prioritise swelling/obstruction over colour.
// CLUSTER: hearing development, bedside hearing tests and pattern-based hearing-loss triage
{MEM-790, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - Hearing HL Child/Baby: child not talking/seems not to hear; ask name/startle/voice response. Also speech delay, incr. gadget vol, academic/behav. issue, family/teacher notice; ?congen. profound HL if early signs; play 'hear games'; counter myth. Babies (6–18m): low noise; sound stimuli: sand-bottle/plastic bag (high freq), 'Eee' (med), 'Ooo' (low); watch visual tracking too.
{MEM-800, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - HL Patterns: Fast = OE/OM, viral; Slow = age, noise; Fluctuate = OME (clears ~3mth). CHL = block; SNHL = inner ear/nerve, Meniere's. 50% HL preventable; immunise; avoid loud noise (plug/muff).
{MEM-810, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - Poor Hearing: OME = blocked/loaded fluctuating hearing after cold; check dull/sucked-in drum or air bubbles. Perf TM: perforation cue; later tympanoplasty/autoinflate.
{MEM-820, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - Sore Ear: AOM, CSOM (common); check tonsil/sinus too; avoid water if perf.
{MEM-830, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - Mid Ear Disease Dynamic: Heal > change to another; re-check 1wk even if 'resolved'; 'simple' OM > rapid mastoiditis.
{MEM-840, LIST, MEM_ENT} - Tuning Fork (512Hz/app): Rinne, Weber; midline?; diff CHL/SNHL; 256Hz OK.
{MEM-850, DO, MEM_ENT} - Speech Recep. Threshold (SRT): Quiet room; test 'better' ear 1st; cover mouth, rub tragus to mask other ear; use familiar local words (Cowboy, Fish, num 2,4,7).
{MEM-860, LIST, MEM_ENT} - Degrees HL: Slight (whisper), Mod (converse), Sev (loud), Profound (deaf); check missed calls/knocks; gauge aid/sign training.
{MEM-870, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - Acoustic Neuroma/Vestibular Schwannoma: Unilateral slow HL + tinnitus/imbalance; ?facial numbness/neurofibromas; needs hearing/balance tests + specialist.
{MEM-880, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - Tinnitus: counsel/adapt; don't dismiss as stress (esp W); pulsatile?; simple sound Tx (fan/radio).
{MEM-890, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - Presbycusis: High freq 1st (W/child voice); face-to-face; ?aid/amplifier.
{MEM-900, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - Otosclerosis/slow CHL: quiet sounds worse over months/years with normal drum and no discharge; no warning unless clearly sudden or neuro/vertigo danger; ask FHx and Rinne/Weber if able; aid ('pocket talker') crucial.
{MEM-910, DO, MEM_ENT} - Hearing aid refused: encourage school use, reduce stigma; check fit/whistle/pain; consider sign/lip-read.
{MEM-920, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - Baby Sleeps Well: Likely no urgent ear prob; Cries suckling (pressure change) = ear prob.
// CLUSTER: practical ear care, foreign-body handling and common nose/throat procedures
{MEM-930, DONT, MEM_ENT} - NEVER buds/sticks in ear canal.
{MEM-940, DO, MEM_ENT} - FBs (Ear/Nose): seed/bean swells with water/oil; ask if clearly visible plus one danger cue: pain, bleeding or drum concern; no routine age/onset. Later: don't push deep; remove only if clearly visible; refer if not seen.
{MEM-950, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - 1-sided nasal discharge: child = foreign body until checked; ask visible object, smell/bleeding. Adult = suspicious mass/septum/allergy; inspect gently.
{MEM-960, DO, MEM_ENT} - Dry Mop: Pre-check no bleed; tissue-twist 'spears'; let wet, rotate gently, repeat till clean; no TM touch.
{MEM-970, DO, MEM_ENT} - Blind ear drops: if drum/TM not visible or FB possible, unsafe; first ask drum/TM visible/perforated plus FB, pain or bleeding; no routine age/onset. Later: clear canal to TM; pt ear up 5min; pump tragus.
{MEM-980, DO, MEM_ENT} - Ear Syringe: Pre-soften wax 2d; control warm water up canal wall (not TM); check often; avoid if surg/perf hist; dizzy > stop/rest.
{MEM-985, DO, MEM_ENT} - Ear discharge: no syringing; inspect canal/TM before drops.
{MEM-990, DO, MEM_ENT} - Epistaxis: do not tilt head back or pack with cotton; lean forward, pinch soft nose 10min; ask blood down throat or breathing trouble. Later: pack/adrenaline/cautery; check BP, anaemia.
{MEM-1000, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - Sinusitis: Usually viral (Sx care); bacterial > ?Abx (M underreport); saline wash, steam; transilluminate (bright torch).
{MEM-1010, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - Barotrauma/ETD: ?Allergy, chron. rhinitis; chew, yawn, decongestant.
{MEM-1020, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - Cheek/parotid swelling worse with chewing/food: check Stensen's duct, fever/mumps/vaccine and sour-food pain; bacterial superinfection later.
{MEM-1030, DO, MEM_ENT} - Oral candidiasis/thrush: wipe-off white mouth patches, sore feeding, nappy rash; nystatin/gentian violet later.
{MEM-1040, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - Nasal polyps: pale bilateral obstructing lumps; if supplied, echo asthma/aspirin; ask smell loss before age/onset; saline/steroid later.
{MEM-1050, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - Deviated Septum: Positional sleep; refer if Sx.
{MEM-1060, CHECK, MEM_ENT} - Branchial Cyst (1-3): Check sinus tract; monitor; excise if Sx; often dismiss (M).
